- Hacking Defined:
Exploiting a sytems vulnerabilities and security controls to gain access to system resources and features,outside the creators's original purpose.


- Ethical Hacking Defined:
Involves the use of hacking methods and tools to discover weakness for system security.


- Skills to be an Ethical Hacker:
Expert with programs and networks(TCP/IP)
Proficient with vulnerability research
Mastery with diverse hacking techniques
Follow a strict code of conduct
Explicit Permissions in writing
Use the same tactics & strategies
Report all of your results


*Type of Pen Tests:
Black Box	|	Gray Box	|	White Box
